uth. Compare Malay bia ( “ cowry ” ) , Thai เบี้ย ( bîia , “ cowry shell; money ” ) , Proto-Mon-Khmer *ɓa(a)j ( “ bean, small weight or coin ” ) > Khasi sbâi ( “ cowry; shell; money ” ) , Khmer ពៃ ( pɨy , “ obsolete small coin ” ) ( Schuessler, 2007 ). Note also Burmese ပဲ ( pai: , “ bean ” ) . Pronunciation:  Mandarin ( Standard ) ( Pinyin ) : bèi ( bei 4 ) (  ( Chengdu , Sichuanese Pinyin ) : bei 4 Cantonese ( Guangzhou – Hong Kong ,  3 ( Taishan , Wiktionary ) : boi 1 Gan ( Wiktionary ) : bi 4 Hakka ( Sixian , PFS ) : pi ( Hailu , HRS ) : bui ˇ ( Meixian , Guangdong ) : bi 4 Jin ( Wiktionary ) : bei 3 Northern Min ( KCR ) : bo̿ Eastern Min ( BUC ) : buói Puxian Min ( Pouseng Ping'ing ): buei 4 Southern Min ( Hokkien , POJ ) : pòe ( Teochew , Peng'im ) : buê 6 / buê 3 ( Leizhou , Leizhou Pinyin ) : bue 3 / bui 3 Wu ( Shanghai , Wugniu ) : 5 pe Xiang ( Changsha , Wiktionary ) : bei 4 Mandarin ( Standard Chinese: ) +     4 Yale : bèi   (bɛj) Sinological  ( Chengdu ) Sichuanese Pinyin : bei 4 Scuanxua Ladinxua Xin Wenz : bei Sinological  Cantonese ( Standard Cantonese , Guangzhou – Hong Kong )  3 Yale : bui  3  3 Sinological  ( Taishanese , Taicheng ) Wiktionary : boi 1 Sinological  Gan ( Nanchang ) Wiktionary : bi 4 Sinological  Hakka ( Sixian , incl. Miaoli and Neipu ) Pha̍k-fa-sṳ : pi Hakka Romanization System : bi Hagfa Pinyim : bi 4  ( Hailu , incl. Zhudong ) Hakka Romanization System : bui ˇ  ( Meixian ) Guangdong : bi 4  Jin ( Taiyuan ) + Wiktionary : bei 3 Sinological  Northern Min ( Jian'ou ) Kienning Colloquial Romanized : bo̿ Sinological  Eastern Min ( Fuzhou ) Bàng-uâ-cê : buói Sinological  Puxian Min ( Putian , Xianyou ) Pouseng Ping'ing : buei 4 Báⁿ-uā-ci̍ : bo̍i Sinological  Southern Min ( Hokkien ) Pe̍h-ōe-jī : pòe Tâi-lô : puè Phofsit Daibuun : poex      ( Teochew ) Peng'im : buê 6 / buê 3 Pe̍h-ōe-jī -like : puĕ / puè Sinological , /pue²¹³/ Note : buê3 - in 寶貝 ／ 宝贝 . ( Leizhou ) Leizhou Pinyin : bue 3 / bui 3 , /pui²¹/ Note : bue3 - vernacular; bui3 